{"title_page": "Kawahigashi Station (Fukushima)", "text_new": "{{short description|Railway station in Sukagawa, Fukushima Prefecture, Japan}}\n{{Unreferenced|date=February 2015}}\n{{Infobox station\n| name        = Kawahigashi Station\n| native_name = \u5ddd\u6771\u99c5\n| native_name_lang = ja\n| type        = \n| image       = JR Kawahigashi sta 001.jpg\n| alt         = \n| caption     = Kawahigashi Station in May 2008\n| other_name  = \n| address     = Kosakuda Nishidate 132, Sukagawa-shi, Fukushima-ken 962-0727\n| country     = Japan\n| coordinates = {{coord|37|16|11|N|140|24|22|E|region:JP-07_type:landmark_source:kolossus-jawiki|display=inline, title}}\n| operator    = [[File:JR logo (east).svg|20px]] [[JR East]]\n| line        = {{Colorbull|Green}} [[Suigun Line]]\n| platforms   = 1 side platform\n| tracks      = 2\n| distance    = 122.2 km from {{STN|Mito|Ibaraki}} \n| connections = \n| structure   = \n| code        = \n| status      = Unstaffed \n| website     = {{official|1=http://www.jreast.co.jp/estation/station/info.aspx?StationCd=533}}\n| opened      = October 10, 1931\n| closed      = \n| former      =  \n| passengers  = \u3000\n| pass_year   = \n| services    = {{Adjacent stations|system=JR East|line=Suigun|left=Izumig\u014d|right=Oshioe|to-right=K\u014driyama}}\n| map_type    = Japan Fukushima Prefecture#Japan   \n| map_dot_label       = Kawahigashi Station\n}}\n \n{{nihongo|'''Kawahigashi Station'''|\u5ddd\u6771\u99c5|Kawahigashi-eki}} is a [[railway station]] in the city of [[Sukagawa, Fukushima]], [[Japan]] operated by the [[East Japan Railway Company]] (JR East).\n\n==Lines==\nKawahigashi Station is served by the [[Suigun Line]], and is located 122.2 rail kilometers from the official starting point of the line at {{STN|Mito|Ibaraki}}. \n\n==Station layout==\nThe station has two opposed [[side platform]]s connected to the station building by a footbridge; however, one of the platforms in no longer in use, and the overhead passageway has been discontinued, rendering the station effectively a single [[side platform]] station serving a single bi-directional track. The station is unattended.\n\n==History==\nKawahigashi Station opened on October 10, 1931. The station was absorbed into the JR East network upon the [[privatization]] of the [[Japanese National Railways]] (JNR) on April 1, 1987.\n\n==Surrounding area==\n* Kawahigashi Post Office\n*Abukuma River\n*Wada no Daibutsu\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of Railway Stations in Japan]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category-inline}}\n* {{official|1=http://www.jreast.co.jp/estation/station/info.aspx?StationCd=533}} {{in lang|ja}}\n\n{{Suigun Line}}\n\n[[Category:Stations of East Japan Railway Company]]\n[[Category:Railway stations in Fukushima Prefecture]]\n[[Category:Suigun Line]]\n[[Category:Railway stations opened in 1931]]\n[[Category:1931 establishments in Japan]]\n[[Category:Sukagawa, Fukushima]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Railway station in Sukagawa, Fukushima Prefecture, Japan}}\n{{Unreferenced|date=February 2015}}\n{{Infobox station\n| name        = Kawahigashi Station\n| native_name = \u5ddd\u6771\u99c5\n| native_name_lang = ja\n| type        = \n| image       = JR Kawahigashi sta 001.jpg\n| alt         = \n| caption     = Kawahigashi Station in May 2008\n| other_name  = \n| address     = Kosakuda Nishidate 132, Sukagawa-shi, Fukushima-ken 962-0727\n| country     = Japan\n| coordinates = {{coord|37|16|11|N|140|24|22|E|region:JP-07_type:landmark_source:kolossus-jawiki|display=inline, title}}\n| operator    = [[File:JR logo (east).svg|20px]] [[JR East]]\n| line        = {{Colorbull|Green}} [[Suigun Line]]\n| platforms   = 1 side platform\n| tracks      = 2\n| distance    = 122.2 km from {{STN|Mito|Ibaraki}} \n| connections = \n| structure   = \n| code        = \n| status      = Unstaffed \n| website     = {{official|1=http://www.jreast.co.jp/estation/station/info.aspx?StationCd=533}}\n| opened      = October 10, 1931\n| closed      = \n| former      =  \n| passengers  = \u3000\n| pass_year   = \n| services    = {{Adjacent stations|system=JR East|line=Suigun|left=Izumig\u014d|right=Oshioe|to-right=K\u014driyama}}\n| map_type    = Japan\n}}\n \n{{nihongo|'''Kawahigashi Station'''|\u5ddd\u6771\u99c5|Kawahigashi-eki}} is a railway station on the [[Suigun Line]] in the city of [[Sukagawa, Fukushima]], [[Japan]] operated by the [[East Japan Railway Company]] (JR East).\n\n==Lines==\nKawahigashi Station is served by the [[Suigun Line]], and is located 122.2 rail kilometers from the official starting point of the line at {{STN|Mito|Ibaraki}}. \n\n==Station layout==\nKawahigashi Station has two opposed [[side platform]]s connected to the station building by a footbridge; however, one of the platforms in no longer in use, and the overhead passageway has been discontinued, rendering the station effectively a single [[side platform]] station serving a single bi-directional track. The station is unattended.\n\n==History==\nKawahigashi Station opened on October 10, 1931. The station was absorbed into the JR East network upon the [[privatization]] of the [[Japanese National Railways]] (JNR) on April 1, 1987.\n\n==Surrounding area==\n* Kawahigashi Post Office\n*Abukuma River\n*Wada no Daibutsu\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of Railway Stations in Japan]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category-inline}}\n* {{official|1=http://www.jreast.co.jp/estation/station/info.aspx?StationCd=533}} {{in lang|ja}}\n\n{{Suigun Line}}\n\n[[Category:Stations of East Japan Railway Company]]\n[[Category:Railway stations in Fukushima Prefecture]]\n[[Category:Suigun Line]]\n[[Category:Railway stations opened in 1931]]\n[[Category:1931 establishments in Japan]]\n[[Category:Sukagawa, Fukushima]]\n", "name_user": "MChew", "label": "safe", "comment": "replace map", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kawahigashi_Station_(Fukushima)"}
